<section class="legal-page" style="padding: 12rem 0 8rem;">
    <div class="container">
        <h1 style="font-size: 3.5rem; color: var(--navy); margin-bottom: 2rem;">Do Not Call (DNC) Policy</h1>
        
        <div class="legal-content">
            <p>At First Home Renovations, we prioritize the sanctity of your home and your personal time. We strictly adhere to federal and state Do Not Call regulations.</p>

            <h3>1. National Registry Compliance</h3>
            <p>We do not place unsolicited marketing calls to numbers listed on the National Do Not Call Registry. We only contact you if you have specifically requested a renovation estimate or consultation through our website.</p>

            <h3>2. Internal Do Not Call List</h3>
            <p>If you no longer wish to be contacted about your home improvement inquiry, you can ask to be placed on our Internal DNC List. Once added, we will not contact you for at least five (5) years unless you initiate a new request.</p>

            <h3>3. How to Opt-Out</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Text:</strong> Reply "STOP" to any SMS message.</li>
                <li><strong>Email:</strong> Send your name and phone number to dnc@firsthomerenovations.com.</li>
                <li><strong>Phone:</strong> Tell any of our project specialists that you wish to be placed on the DNC list.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>4. Contractor Communication</h3>
            <p>Independent contractors in our network manage their own communication logs. If you are already in discussions with a contractor, you must inform them directly if you wish to stop receiving calls from their specific business.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
